# Up Final Migration Workflow Rule

## Migration Strategy
- Migrate in phases: `P0 -> P1 -> P2`.
- Every task must be tagged as one of:
  - `reuse` (along with existing implementation)
  - `refactor` (restructure while preserving intent)
  - `defer` (schedule for later)

## Priority Definition
- **P0 (Must work first)**:
  - Entitlement foundation (`purchase_status`, `subscription_status`, `is_pro`)
  - Core local-first data path (assessment/history/radar/widgets)
  - Leaderboard access gating (Pro check before entry/upload)
  - Firebase hot-path optimization (cache + throttling + summary-only writes)
- **P1 (Stabilize + clarity)**:
  - Subscription flow integration and restore handling
  - Cloud sync stabilization for eligible Pro users
  - Six-dimension scoring alignment (including arm size and grip strength)
- **P2 (Polish)**:
  - Visual refinement
  - Animation/micro-interactions
  - Non-critical UI enhancements

## Scope Guard
- Do not mix large visual redesign with critical data-flow refactor in one task.
- Ship incremental, testable slices.
- If requirements are unclear, default to preserving existing behavior.
- Remove honor-certification logic and ad-related logic as independent scoped changes.

## Definition of Done (Per Task)
- Core flow still works end-to-end.
- No new hardcoded text if i18n path exists.
- No direct coupling introduced between UI and external service SDK.
- Non-Pro users generate zero leaderboard Firestore traffic.
